---
import AboutHeroImage from "../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg";
import AboutMePhoto from "../assets/AboutMePhoto.png";
import Layout from "../layouts/BlogPost.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About Me"
  heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
  description="Welcome to my blog!"
  pubDate={new Date("April 01 2026")}
  showAuthorCard={false}
>
  <p>Hi, I'm Nikka.</p>

  <p>
    I'm a developer by trade, traveler by habit, and, for the past few years,
    someone who has been very slowly learning the difference between waiting and
    living.
  </p>

  <p>
    A few years ago, everything went on pause. I was diagnosed with thyroid
    cancer, and for a while, life became a waiting room. Waiting for results,
    waiting for recovery, waiting to feel like myself again. What I didn't
    expect was what the waiting would teach me. Gratitude showed up slowly, then
    all at once. So did clarity. And eventually, so did everything I'd been
    afraid I might miss.
  </p>

  <p>
    I used to put things on pause. Waiting until I was ready. Waiting until it
    was the right time. Cancer has a way of ending that habit. Now I try to live
    like everything counts, because it does. There's a reason for everything.
    Nothing is actually on pause. It's all on purpose.
  </p>

  <p>
    This blog is where I put the things I want to remember, and the things I
    think might help someone else who is quietly going through the same thing. I
    write about life after Thyroid cancer, building things as a developer,
    managing money without losing my mind, traveling whenever I can, and
    whatever else I happen to be figuring out that week.
  </p>

  <p>Welcome to my little corner of the internet.</p>
</Layout>
